@startuml
title Activity Diagram: Manage Execution State

' Text Description:
' 1. The system captures the latest data from the active execution.
' 2. The system accesses the specific Workflow Instance record.
' 3. In parallel, the system updates the variables in the Execution Context and the current step pointer.
' 4. Simultaneously, a new entry is appended to the Step History.
' 5. The system commits all state changes to persistent storage.

start
:Capture execution data;
:Access Workflow Instance;
fork
  :Update Execution Context and Step Pointer;
fork again
  :Append Step History entry;
end fork
:Commit state changes;
stop
@enduml